  <!-- Section: FAQ -->
  <section id="faq" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I get Thai citizenship through investment?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          No. Thailand does not offer citizenship through investment. The path to citizenship requires 5+ years residence (often interpreted as 10+), Thai language proficiency, and discretionary approval—it's very difficult and rarely granted. Most expats accept permanent long-term visas (Elite, LTR) as the practical endpoint.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I work remotely on Thailand Elite?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Technically, Thailand Elite doesn't include work authorization. However, remote work for non-Thai employers/clients is widely tolerated and practiced by Elite members. You cannot work for Thai companies or Thai-based clients. If you need formal work authorization, consider LTR Visa which explicitly includes work permit.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What happens if Thailand Elite is discontinued?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Your membership remains valid for its full term even if the program closes to new members. Thailand Privilege Card (government-owned) honors existing memberships. The program has operated since 2003 and shows no signs of discontinuation—it generates government revenue and attracts desirable visitors.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I buy property in Thailand?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Foreigners can own condos (up to 49% of building's units) outright. Land ownership is generally prohibited. Options include: leasing land (30-year leases, renewable), owning through Thai company (complex, risks), or marriage to Thai citizen (some rights). Consult a lawyer before property purchase—rules are complex.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How does 90-day reporting work?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Most Thai visas require notifying Immigration of your address every 90 days. Done at Immigration office, by mail, or online (TM47). Fines for missing it (฿2,000). Elite members can do simplified online notification. LTR has 1-year reporting instead. Mark your calendar—this is commonly forgotten.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Thailand Elite worth the cost?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          For long-term residents, absolutely. At ฿600,000 for 5 years (~$5,000/year), you get: no visa runs, no 90-day in-person reporting, VIP airport service, unlimited entries, and peace of mind. Compare to visa runs (time, cost, stress) and yearly visa renewals. If you're staying 3+ years, Elite typically pays for itself in convenience.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section: Final Verdict -->
  <section id="verdict" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Final Verdict</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Thailand offers the most accessible and hassle-free long-term residence options in Southeast Asia. Thailand Elite provides 5-20 years of stay for a one-time payment, with VIP perks that make expat life genuinely easier. The LTR Visa adds work permit and tax benefits for those who qualify. For investors and high-net-worth individuals, Thailand delivers exceptional lifestyle value.
    </p>

    <p class="mb-4">
      The trade-offs are clear: no citizenship pathway, property ownership restrictions, and work rights depend on visa type. Thailand also lacks the political stability and rule of law found in Singapore or Western countries. But for those seeking tropical lifestyle, low costs, excellent healthcare, and welcoming culture, Thailand remains unmatched.
    </p>

    <p class="mb-6">
      Health insurance is practically essential regardless of visa requirements. Thailand's private hospitals are world-class and affordable with insurance—expensive without it. Budget ฿4,000-15,000/month for comprehensive coverage and choose a provider with strong Thai hospital networks.
    </p>

    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Bottom Line</h3>
      <p class="text-primary-800 mb-4">
        Thailand suits investors and high-net-worth individuals seeking Southeast Asian lifestyle, excellent healthcare access, and hassle-free long-term residence. Thailand Elite offers the simplest path for most (฿600K-1M, 5-20 years). LTR Visa adds work permit and tax benefits for qualified applicants. Come with realistic expectations about citizenship limits and property restrictions—but enjoy exceptional value and lifestyle.
      </p>
